  52:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****   @verbatim
  53:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** ==============================================================================
  54:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                       ##### Simple mode v.s. waveform mode #####
  55:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** ==============================================================================
  56:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****   [..] The HRTIM HAL API is split into 2 categories:
  57:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Simple functions: these functions allow for using a HRTIM timer as a
  58:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        general purpose timer with high resolution capabilities.
  59:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        HRTIM simple modes are managed through the set of functions named
  60:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        HAL_HRTIM_Simple<Function>. These functions are similar in name and usage
  61:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        to the one defined for the TIM peripheral. When a HRTIM timer operates in
  62:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        simple mode, only a very limited set of HRTIM features are used.
  63:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        Following simple modes are proposed:
  64:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)Output compare mode,
  65:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)PWM output mode,
  66:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)Input capture mode,
  67:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)One pulse mode.
  68:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Waveform functions: These functions allow taking advantage of the HRTIM
  69:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        flexibility to produce numerous types of control signal. When a HRTIM timer
  70:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        operates in waveform mode, all the HRTIM features are accessible without
  71:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        any restriction. HRTIM waveform modes are managed through the set of
  72:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        functions named HAL_HRTIM_Waveform<Function>
  73:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                       ##### How to use this driver #####
  74:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** ==============================================================================
  75:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     [..]
  76:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#)Initialize the HRTIM low level resources by implementing the
  77:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         HAL_HRTIM_MspInit() function:
  78:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Enable the HRTIM clock source using __HRTIMx_CLK_ENABLE()
  79:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Connect HRTIM pins to MCU I/Os
  80:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++) Enable the clock for the HRTIM GPIOs using the following
  81:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   function: __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE()
  82:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++) Configure these GPIO pins in Alternate Function mode using
  83:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   HAL_GPIO_Init()
  84:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)When using DMA to control data transfer (e.g HAL_HRTIM_SimpleBaseStart_DMA())
  85:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Enable the DMAx interface clock using __DMAx_CLK_ENABLE()
  86:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Initialize the DMA handle
  87:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Associate the initialized DMA handle to the appropriate DMA
  88:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  handle of the HRTIM handle using __HAL_LINKDMA()
ARM GAS  C:\Users\simon\AppData\Local\Temp\ccCS5KQ2.s 			page 3


  89:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Initialize the DMA channel using HAL_DMA_Init()
  90:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Configure the priority and enable the NVIC for the transfer
  91:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  complete interrupt on the DMA channel using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority()
  92:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
  93:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)In case of using interrupt mode (e.g HAL_HRTIM_SimpleBaseStart_IT())
  94:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Configure the priority and enable the NVIC for the concerned
  95:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  HRTIM interrupt using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
  96:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
  97:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Initialize the HRTIM HAL using HAL_HRTIM_Init(). The HRTIM configuration
  98:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        structure (field of the HRTIM handle) specifies which global interrupt of
  99:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        whole HRTIM must be enabled (Burst mode period, System fault, Faults).
 100:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        It also contains the HRTIM external synchronization configuration. HRTIM
 101:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        can act as a master (generating a synchronization signal) or as a slave
 102:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        (waiting for a trigger to be synchronized).
 103:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 104:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Configure HRTIM resources shared by all HRTIM timers
 105:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Burst Mode Controller:
 106:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_BurstModeConfig(): configures the HRTIM burst mode
 107:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      controller: operating mode (continuous or one-shot mode), clock
 108:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      (source, prescaler) , trigger(s), period, idle duration.
 109:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)External Events Conditioning:
 110:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_EventConfig(): configures the conditioning of an
 111:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      external event channel: source, polarity, edge-sensitivity.
 112:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      External event can be used as triggers (timer reset, input
 113:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      capture, burst mode, ADC triggers, delayed protection)
 114:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      They can also be used to set or reset timer outputs. Up to
 115:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      10 event channels are available.
 116:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_EventPrescalerConfig(): configures the external
 117:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      event sampling clock (used for digital filtering).
 118:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Fault Conditioning:
 119:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_FaultConfig(): configures the conditioning of a
 120:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      fault channel: source, polarity, edge-sensitivity. Fault
 121:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      channels are used to disable the outputs in case of an
 122:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      abnormal operation. Up to 5 fault channels are available.
 123:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_FaultPrescalerConfig(): configures the fault
 124:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      sampling clock (used for digital filtering).
 125:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_FaultModeCtl(): Enables or disables fault input(s)
 126:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      circuitry. By default all fault inputs are disabled.
 127:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)ADC trigger:
 128:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_ADCTriggerConfig(): configures the source triggering
 129:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      the update of the ADC trigger register and the ADC trigger.
 130:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      4 independent triggers are available to start both the regular
 131:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      and the injected sequencers of the 2 ADCs
 132:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 133:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Configure HRTIM timer time base using HAL_HRTIM_TimeBaseConfig(). This
 134:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          function must be called whatever the HRTIM timer operating mode is
 135:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (simple v.s. waveform). It configures mainly:
 136:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)The HRTIM  timer counter operating mode (continuous v.s. one shot)
 137:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)The HRTIM  timer clock prescaler
 138:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)The HRTIM  timer period
 139:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)The HRTIM  timer repetition counter
 140:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 141:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      *** If the HRTIM timer operates in simple mode ***
