 164:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      *** If the HRTIM timer operates in waveform mode ***
 165:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      ====================================================
 166:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 167:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Completes waveform timer configuration
 168:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformTimerConfig(): configuration of a HRTIM timer
 169:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   operating in wave form mode mainly consists in:
 170:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the HRTIM timer interrupts and DMA requests.
 171:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the half mode for the HRTIM timer.
 172:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Defining how the HRTIM timer reacts to external synchronization input.
 173:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the push-pull mode for the HRTIM timer.
 174:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the fault channels for the HRTIM timer.
 175:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the dead-time insertion for the HRTIM timer.
 176:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Setting the delayed protection mode for the HRTIM timer (source and outputs
 177:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      on which the delayed protection are applied).
 178:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Specifying the HRTIM timer update and reset triggers.
 179:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Specifying the HRTIM timer registers update policy (e.g. pre-load enabling).
 180:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_TimerEventFilteringConfig(): configures external
 181:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   event blanking and windowing circuitry of a HRTIM timer:
 182:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Blanking:  to mask external events during a defined  time period a defined tim
 183:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Windowing, to enable external events only during a defined time period
 184:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_DeadTimeConfig(): configures the dead-time insertion
 185:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   unit for a HRTIM timer. Allows to generate a couple of
 186:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   complementary signals from a single reference waveform,
 187:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   with programmable delays between active state.
 188:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_ChopperModeConfig(): configures the parameters of
 189:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   the high-frequency carrier signal added on top of the timing
 190:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   unit output. Chopper mode can be enabled or disabled for each
 191:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                    timer output separately (see  HAL_HRTIM_WaveformOutputConfig()).
 192:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_BurstDMAConfig(): configures the burst DMA burst
 193:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   controller. Allows having multiple HRTIM registers updated
 194:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   with a single DMA request. The burst DMA operation is started
 195:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   by calling HAL_HRTIM_BurstDMATransfer().
 196:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformCompareConfig():configures the compare unit
 197:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   of a HRTIM timer. This operation consists in setting the
 198:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   compare value and possibly specifying the auto delayed mode
 199:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   for compare units 2 and 4 (allows to have compare events
 200:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   generated relatively to capture events). Note that when auto
 201:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   delayed mode is needed, the capture unit associated to the
 202:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   compare unit must be configured separately.
