 317:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 318:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 319:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      By default, after the HAL_HRTIM_Init() and when the state is HAL_HRTIM_STATE_RESET
 320:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions (e.g HAL_HRTIM_Fault1Callback)
 321:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are reset to the legacy
 322:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      weak functions in the HAL_HRTIM_Init()/ HAL_HRTIM_DeInit() only when these
 323:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      callbacks are null (not registered beforehand). If MspInit or MspDeInit are
 324:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      not null, the HAL_HRTIM_Init()/ HAL_HRTIM_DeInit() keep and use the user
 325:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 326:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 327:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 328:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_HRTIM_STATE_READY state only.
 329:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 330:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      in HAL_HRTIM_STATE_READY or HAL_HRTIM_STATE_RESET states, thus registered
 331:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 332:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 333:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      using HAL_HRTIM_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_HRTIM_DeInit()
 334:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      or HAL_HRTIM_Init() function.
 335:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 336:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 337:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      When the compilation flag USE_HAL_HRTIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 338:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all
 339:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 340:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 341:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_hrtim.c ****   @endverbatim
